  "body": "The example Kubernetes documents shows how to create a cluster and consume block storage within the cluster. There should also be an example of creating an object storage from a cluster for applications internal to the cluster to use.\r\n\r\nOnce a service endpoint is created it should be trivial to also expose that endpoint external to the cluster via a load balancer or ingress controller.\r\n\r\nWould really like to have some examples on this because the existing `rook` commands in the documentation https://github.com/rook/rook/blob/master/Documentation/client.md#object-storage obviously don't work from outside the cluster.",
